Adds structured organization and detailed presentation for tour guides
Enhances the tour guides' page by grouping guides by region for better navigation and organization.
Introduces a more comprehensive description of guides, including their expertise and specialties.
Implements a selection process section to highlight the criteria for guide selection, emphasizing local expertise, training, and storytelling abilities.

Add new tour constants for various destinations including Nha Trang, Paris, Philadelphia, Queenstown, Rome, Sacred Valley, San Diego, San Francisco, Savannah, Seattle, Shanghai, Singapore, St. Petersburg, Thessaloniki, Tokyo, Tuscany, Vienna, and Washington. Each tour includes details such as title, description, images, duration, price, rating, tags, family-friendliness, historical significance, romantic appeal, local experience, tour guide, category, and FAQs.

Updates tour interface to use tourCategoryId
Refactors the Tour interface to replace the tourGuideId property with tourCategoryId for better clarity and accuracy in representing the relationship with TourCategory.
This change enhances the data model by correctly associating the category of the tour rather than the guide, improving overall code consistency and maintainability.

Refactors getTourData to streamline city-based tour fetching
Updates the getTourData function to accept a city parameter instead of tour category and tour name.
Implements formatting for the city input to create a tourID, enhancing the logic for dynamically importing tour modules based on city names.
This change simplifies function usage and improves code maintainability.

Adds tour categories display in TourPackages component
Implements a mapping of tour categories to render their titles, descriptions, and associated tags in the TourPackages component.
This enhancement improves the user interface by providing more detailed information about available tour categories, making it easier for users to understand their options.

Improves city, region, and country formatting in get function
Enhances the formatting of city, region, and country names in the getCityAttractions function to ensure proper camelCase and accent removal.
This change improves the consistency and reliability of the formatted strings used for fetching attractions, ultimately leading to better data handling and user experience.

Refactors attraction interface for improved clarity
Updates the attraction interface to replace `priceRange` and `priceCategory` with `entryFee` and `entryFeeCategory`, enhancing semantic clarity.
Ensures `priceRange` is explicitly defined with specific values and makes `isFree` a required field to better represent the attraction's attributes.

Improves price filtering logic for attractions
Enhances the attraction price filtering by incorporating entry fee and entry fee category into the decision-making process.
Updates the UI to display entry fees alongside titles, providing clearer information to users.
This change ensures a more accurate representation of attractions based on the user-selected filters, improving the overall experience.
